<br>
The Vah Shir got &quot;transported&quot; up here in some sort of large natural or supernatural event (presumably due to the Kerran/Heretic war and/or the event that created the Hole). They were the first &quot;modern Norrathians&quot; to get to Luclin, but had no ability to make quadroliths (spires).<br>
<br>
The only reason the Combine Empire knew there was a quadrolith on Luclin is because some of their greatest minds &quot;sensed&quot; it there.<br>
<br>
The Loyalists, led by Imeratur Tsaph Katta, took one-way passage to Luclin to flee a coup attempt by Seru. Then split into the Shadow Haven group (who stayed near Nexus to investigate learning how to return to Norrath) and the Katta Castellum group (who ventured to Luclin's surface to restart the Combine Empire as they saw it). The Inquisition of Seru followed them later to the moon and founded Santus Seru.<br>
<br>
None of these three factions had the power to make quadroliths either. The House of Midst in Shadow Haven had been studying the means to return to Norrath for a long time, but it took Al'Kabor of Norrath to recently figure out how to open two-way travel between Norrath and Luclin.<br>
<br>
Anyway, my only point is that no one currently knows how to make quadroliths, and Luclin was settled after the time when the ancients built the quadroliths, so there is no reason why there should be more spires on Luclin.<br>
<br>
As a side note, the druids are attuned to Norrath and no druid rings are found on Luclin either <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
